EventItemActionText: This Communication was Rcvd, Ord, Prnt, Fld by Council
EventItemTitle:
Designation of Minority Whip
Pursuant to Rule 4.10 of the Council of the City of New York and Paragraph 5 of the Bylaws of the Minority Delegation of the same, I hereby designate and appoint Joseph C. Borelli as Minority Whip of the Council of the City of New York, effective December 7, 2015. 
Signed: Steven Matteo, Minority Leader
EventItemMatterName: Designation of Joseph C. Borelli as Minority Whip of the Council of the City of New York, effective 12/7/15.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Rights
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter and the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to making improvements to clarify and strengthen the human rights law, and to repeal and replace section 8-102 of the administrative code of the city of New York, relating to definitions of terms in the human rights law, and to repeal sections 8-103, 8-104, 8-105 and 8-106 of the administrative code of the city of New York, relating to the functions, powers and duties of the commission on human rights and its relations with city departments and agencies
EventItemMatterName: Making improvements to clarify and strengthen the human rights law.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: Resolution proclaiming the month of November as Hip-Hop Month in the City of New York and urging the New York State Legislature and Governor to declare the month of November as Hip-Hop Appreciation Month in the State of New York.
EventItemMatterName: Proclaiming the month of November as Hip-Hop Month in NYC.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Women's Issues
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the United States Congress and the State of New York to support a womans right to abortion and to oppose sex-selective abortion bans that perpetuate racial stereotypes and undermine access to care.
EventItemMatterName: Support a womans right to abortion and to oppose sex-selective abortion bans that perpetuate racial stereotypes and undermine access to care.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the Metropolitan Transportation Authority, the Governor, and the State Legislature to prohibit advertisements for alcoholic beverages on subways, buses, and other New York City Transit property
